description:
For a change tonight I had a decent sky.  It was relatively dark, clear, and transparent.   For years
I've wanted to try and  image NGC 6960  but I just never got around to it.  To be honest I really
felt that it was an object outside of my method of imaging.   Most images that I liked of this
object were taken with very long exposures and appropriate filters.   Anyway I decided to try
and image it tonight.   I did manage to get an image and I'm pleased with that.  It is pitiful
compared to a lot of the images I've seen of this object.   However the image I got tonight
does give me hope that it is possible to get a decent image once I learn what to do when I
image the object and what is needed to properly process an image of the object.  With all of
that said please enjoy my first image of NGC 6960 the Witches Broom.
title: NGC 6960 the Witches Broom
